		</font>
		<hr size="1">Ok ive sat here and read each one of the posts for this topic and im afraid ill have to disagree if those who say not much money can be made from port. I'm not sure how it is on other server but i play Fennin Ro and i still always see ppl looking for port. I myself have made over 1k a day from port. Now granted its not easily done. You have to do port after port after port but ive port for 4 hours before and came up with 1k. Especially to the rich higher lvls ive had some give me as much as 200pp a port just because they really needed to be somewhere soon. Plus ive gotten good items from ppl that they did need and i just turn around and sell them for profit. On top of all that porting can be more benifical than just money you can also make good friends that way. Granted since the books have come into play i havent ported as much but that is only because i choose not to. I'm more concerned on lvling to get the higher ports that ppl want. HGs are a great source for money i myself often hunt them in rathe just to get some money while i get exp. Plus hunting them giving you a broke from the long days of porting. In short, port can make you good money if you work hard at it. At the same time so can fighting. All you need to do is use both abilities to your advantage. Once you get tired of hunting dont just sit around go look around zones and find out where you see alot of ppl calling out for ports. To help you out make a hotkey telling where all you can port to. Then just go back and forth through the zones that have alot of ppl in them and /ooc where all you can port to. Once that gets old go back to fighting and just keep switching back and forth to keep yourself amused.</P><P>Ethman LvL 40 druid<BR>Fennin Ro<BR>&lt;Ruckus&gt;<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
