		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=62&FN=Druid&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1968859&TN=Porting+and+making+money&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1971960&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">A very tired subject, but I'll again offer my opinion--</P><P>Can money be made porting? Yes! Is it worth it? Not really!!</P><P>It isn't so much the fact that money can't be made porting, good money too, its the fact that its very very random. I've seen very rich people donate 10p, and i've seen poor people (like myself) donate 30p. I'll get a rare occasion in which someone donates 200p. That's always nice. One freak night, 2 groups of people pst'd me in like 5 minutes...and from those 2 groups I made almost 400p. Both wanted to go to CS (one wanted a ride back and forth, but it was still pretty sweet). that just shows how random it is. In those 5 minuts, the only thing I had going for me was that I was listed as a lvl 50 druid. I didn't /ooc or anything. </P><P>I've done it for hours and hours and hours, in one session, and made like 200p over the course of a few days with those kind of sessions. Had I hunted, I probably would have made a similar amount of cash---maybe not quite as much---but I also could have picked up a lucky item and definately gotten decent exp. None of this is for lack of effort: I had over 3 pages of /oocs which are absolutely HILLARIOUS!! And, heck, maybe business is better nowadays cuz i'm guessing less people port now that pretty much everyone has PoP. But, then again, most people that have PoP are looking for ports that lowbi druids don't have: ports like Skyfire, CS and Emerald Jungle. Ports taht you have to worry about a dragon slaying you upon destination if you aren't at least dubious w/CoV (which took 4 or 5 Kael raids and several hours of camping various giants across GD and elsewhere)...not exactly an easy thing to do. </P><P>But, I will offer this: some people have a knack at making money in some sort of fashion. Where many JCers lose money, some have that 'nack' and make money. Were I (like many) have found porting to be a waste of time, others have a certain knack and make lots of money. Were I have to sell stuff in /auc for half its real market value or often half of its 20percent off price), other people are able to make tons of cash in the bazaar buying and selling. Some people are lucky in drops and stuff. </P><P>Some people aren't. Each to their own. <BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
